    "Since chest CT scans have a variable spatial resolution, we resample to voxel spacing 0.7 × 0.7 × 1 mm 3.",
    "Each scan is rotated in 7 angles, each spaced 45 degrees apart that is 45°, 90°, 135°, 180°, 225°, 270°, 315°.",
    "C. PROPOSED LMLCC-NET The architecture of the proposed backbone 3D CNN model is shown in Fig. 3.",
    "It uses binary cross-entropy loss, and the CNNs use ReLU activation and batch normalization for hierarchical feature extraction after each convolutional layer during training.The images are first fed into the feature extractor, which consists of twelve 3-D convolution layers with filters of size 3 × 3 × 3.",
    "It also employs four MaxPooling and two Dropout layers to reduce dimensionality and prevent overfitting, respectively."
